Even More Python for Beginners: Data Tools by Microsoft

Aspiring data-science and machine-learning developers now have more Microsoft-made free video tutorials to learn how to build software in Python, one of today's most popular and versatile programming languages.

The new More Python for Beginners series consists of 20 videos that run between two minutes and 15 minutes each. It covers working with files, lambdas or 'anonymous functions',

And object-oriented programming and each tutorial are followed by a short demo video. The tutors also introduce some newer functionality to support asynchronous development through async/await.

Here I successfully completed Certificate of Completion for the amazing "Software Engineering Virtual Experience" from JPMorgan Chase & Co. and InsideSherpa.
The concept of elucidating the aspects of software development and its tools, namely; Python, Git, React, TypeScript, Web Applications, Technical Communication, Financial Analysis and Data Visualization was phenomenal and worth effort. It involves the JPMorgan Chase framework 
hashtag
#Perspective tool which is used to allow users to present and manipulate data feeds visually in web applications. This virtual experience promotes the application of technical skills to a hypothetical request from the firm‚Äôs trading floor to analyze and visualize data in a new way. 
Learning exhibits 4 modules:-
1. Interface with a stock price data feed
2. Use JPMorgan Chase frameworks and tools
3. Display data visually for traders
4. Bonus task: Open source contribution

Here is a data definition for measuring time:
(define-struct time (hours minutes))
; A Time is a (make-time Hour Minute)
; interpretation: (make-time h m) is the time  
; expressed in h hours and m minutes
; 
; ‚Äì An Hour is a NaturalNumber between 0 and 11
; ‚Äì A Minute is a NaturalNumber between 0 and 59
Design the function tock, which adds one minute to the given time.

Design the function time->text, which converts a time to a text. The text should look like the display of a common alarm clock, i.e., it should separate the minutes from the hours with a colon. Hint: a text is an image, not a string, but you will need a string version of the time, too. See the HelpDesk for more on the text function.

After you have developed these functions, add a main function, which launches a big-bang program to animate the time.

*How the smallest of things can bring the biggest changes

Just a week ago, I wrote about how being disciplined helped get through a frustrating week of programming. I code daily and I love it but that week was terrible due to various issues.

In the code editor, you can use different color themes and font styles. I have always stuck to only one font style but I like to change the color theme around every two months.

Yesterday, I got a glimpse of something as small as changing the color theme can drastically change your coding skills.

I was using a light theme from the past 2 months but yesterday I switched it to the dark one. This was the exact theme I used in my toughest project until now. 

That project was delivered a year ago and I have gone sleepless nights to finish the project. As far as I can remember, I have never been that much concentrated on something else before.

I still remember some of the code, issues, and that feeling of focused hard work.

This is the fun part. Somehow that vibe and the theme made a friendly association in my mind and now when I switched back to that theme, I suddenly got into that vibe which resulted in deep work.

Agarwal Packers and Movers:
Turning Point for their Success
----------------------------------
Ramesh Agarwal was working for Indian Air Force.
After retirement, he founded Agarwal Packers in 1987.
He started his business with door-to-door packaging and later he expanded to warehousing, logistics, and infrastructure.
*
Earlier, Samsung and LG were using other companies for transporting their inventory.
And they were losing 25% of inventory during transit, due to breakage.
When Agarwal started transporting their inventory, the breakage was reduced to 2%.
*
Imagine, for two famous electronics companies, he reduced the breakage from 25% to 2%.
Not an easy task...
Only the committed people can do that!
That was the turning point for Agarwal.
And this is the only packing and moving company which is approved by the Indian Banks  Association.
The revenue of Agarwal Packers and Movers is more than Rs 400 crores.

What is the concurrent mode in react?


React is continuously adding new powerful features to its core API‚Äôs and speedily adapting to a better way of programming. Last time the react team came up with the hooks which are a cool and smart feature for functional programming. Now its time for introducing concurrency in react!
So what is concurrency at all?
If you start searching in google you can see thousands of examples and definitions for concurrency in computer-science, many of them play around with the classical dining philosopher problem. But in our case react is going to solve a very simple problem that modern JavaScript libraries haven‚Äôt addressed yet.
The non-blocking rendering
Typically the modern UI libraries do not support interrupting the rendering process. This is called the blocking rendering, now react is going to make it non-blocking. That is the rendering is Interruptible.

Looking to learn Nodejs?

How about starting by learning the following 5 things?

1. The Javascript standard ECMAScript: learning this will help you understand what JS features are supported in your Nodejs version and what is not. 
2. The languages in which you can write Nodejs applications. Namely Javascript or Typescript.
3. The Observer pattern, as Nodejs applications heavily rely on this design pattern.
4. The Callback pattern which supplements the Observer pattern in carrying out executions.
5. Basics of the V8 engine and how it executes the Javascript code that you write. It's important not to go too deep into this has it can be quite complex to understand at first.

Closures in Javascript are possible because of two things:

1. Functions are first-class citizens. We can pass functions around like data ‚Äî like any other type in Javascript.

2. Lexical scope: Based on where our code is written, the Javascript engine knows before we even run the code what variables each function has access to.

And that's what a closure is ‚Äî a combination of a function and the lexical environment from which it was declared.

Closures allow a function to access variables from an enclosing scope or environment even after it leaves the scope in which it was declared.

They have two main benefits:
  1. They can be very memory efficient.
  2. They allow us to do Encapsulation.
